three diff scopes of css

local internal and external
local - confined to a single element
internal - affect elements in an entire page
external - can affect multiple pages

class selector applies to tags

html - content
css - styling

/* this is a comment in css */

#id - unique identifier for a single element
. class - applies to multiple elements
element - applies to all elements of that type
* - universal selector applies to all elements

id overrides stuff


/Grouping
when several selectors share the same declarations
grouped into a comma-separated list
h1, h2, h3 {font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;}

Universal selector
* {border: 1px solid red;}




nesting
h1 em {color: red;}

tope selectorif selector class selector
